President Cyril Ramaphosa initially received a cold welcome with jeers from the crowd at the state funeral of former Zimbabwean president, Robert Mugabe in Harare. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa initially received a cold welcome with jeers fromÂ the crowd at the state funeral of former Zimbabwean president, Robert Mugabe in Harare. He was interrupted several times at the start of his speech. But after apologising for the recent xenophobic attacks in South Africa - the crowd cheered. READ: Ramaphosa, Mbeki to attend Mugabe official state funeral Ramaphosa and former President Thabo Mbeki are among the guests. Mugabe died in Singapore at the age of 95. He will be buried at Heroes Acre in Harare. The exact date of the burial has not yet been set, but can only happen after a mausoleum is built, which could take up to 30 days.